	<P xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" paraDef="topic_title"
		id="#dita-equation-domain-mathml-support">DITA equation domain (&lt;mathml&gt;) support</P>
	<P paraDef="body">MiramoDesigner includes support for two 'MathMLDef' format definitions,
		mathml-block and mathml-inline, which may be used to control the appearance of DITA equation
		domain &lt;mathml&gt; elements.</P>
	<P paraDef="body">Note that the MathMLDef preference must be enabled via <Font
			xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="menucascade"><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
				>Edit</Font><Var varDef="menucascadeseparator"/><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
				>Preferences</Font></Font>, as shown below: <Tbl tblDef="fig"><TblColumn width="1*"
					><TblColumnFormat align="start"
					/></TblColumn><TblTitle><!--topic/title parent fig count= outputclass=--><!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]--><P
					xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" paraDef="figureTitle"
					id="#fig_t2k_s1n_ppb">Enabling MathMLDef support in
					preferences</P></TblTitle><Row><Cell> <AFrame
						xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" wrap="Y" position="below" crop="N"
						startIndent="inherit" align="start"><Image
							file="graphics/mathml_preferences.png" keepAspectRatio="Y"
							shrinkToFit="Y"/></AFrame>
				</Cell></Row></Tbl></P>
	<P paraDef="body">The MathMLDef format definitions and properties may now be accessed via <Font
			xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="menucascade"><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
				>More</Font><Var varDef="menucascadeseparator"/><Font fontDef="uicontrol"
				>MathMLDef</Font></Font>:</P>
	<P paraDef="body">
		<Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="menucascade">
			<Font fontDef="uicontrol">
				<AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start"
					verticalShift="0pt">
					<Image file="graphics/more_button.png" width="72pt" keepAspectRatio="Y"/>
				</AFrame>
			</Font>
			<Var varDef="menucascadeseparator"/>
			<Font fontDef="uicontrol">
				<AFrame wrap="Y" position="inline" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start"
					verticalShift="0pt">
					<Image file="graphics/mathml_properties.png" width="70mm" keepAspectRatio="Y"/>
				</AFrame>
			</Font>
		</Font>
	</P>
	<P paraDef="body">The plugin supports the following DITA math elements, whose appearance is
		controlled by the MathMLDef format definitions in the MFD template, as follows: </P>
	<ParaGroup paraGroupDef="ul">
		<!--topic/li-->
		<!--makeListPara li-->
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1" id="#ul_wqd_dj3_ghb" numberValue="1" withPrevious="Y"
			>equation-block</P>
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1" id="#ul_wqd_dj3_ghb" listLabel="N">Use the
			&lt;equation-block&gt; element to represent an equation that is presented as a separate
			block within a text flow. Block equations can be numbered. &lt;equation-block&gt;
			elements are formatted using the <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
				fontDef="codeph">mathml-block</Font> MathMLDef.</P>

		<!--topic/li-->
		<!--makeListPara li-->
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1">equation-figure</P>
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1" listLabel="N">Use the &lt;equation-figure&gt; element to
			represent an equation that functions as form of figure or display. Display equations are
			intended to be numbered when numbering is desired. &lt;equation-figure&gt; equations are
			wrapped in a 'equation-figure' table, which allows for different numbering sequences for
			equation titles.</P>

		<!--topic/li-->
		<!--makeListPara li-->
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1">equation-inline</P>
		<P paraDef="unorderedlistitem1" listLabel="N">Use the &lt;equation-inline&gt; element to
			represent an equation that is presented inline within a paragraph or similar context.
			Inline equations are not intended to be numbered. &lt;equation-inline&gt; equations are
			are formatted using the <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="codeph"
				>mathml-inline</Font> MathMLDef.</P>

	</ParaGroup>
	<P paraDef="body"><Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="codeph"
			>equation-inline</Font> and <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
			fontDef="codeph">equation-block</Font> MathMLDefs may be used to set default font
		characteristics (font family, pointsize and text color) for &lt;mathml&gt; equations, as
		well as spacing and positioning properties. </P>
</MiramoXML>
